<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> Associates speculated about his intellectual connection to the Virgin Mary, one saying, "He [McLuhan] had a direct connection with the Blessed Virgin Mary... He alluded to it very briefly once, almost fearfully, in a please-don't-laugh-at-me tone. He didn't say, "I know this because the Blessed Virgin Mary told me," but it was clear from what he said that one of the reasons he was so sure about certain things was that the Virgin had certified his understanding of them." (cited in Marchand, p. 51).</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFFitterman">Fitterman, Lisa (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2008-04-19"><a href="/wiki/2008" title="2008">2008</a>-<a href="/wiki/April_19" title="April 19">04-19</a></span>). <a href="http://www.theglobeandmail.com/servlet/story/LAC.20080419.OBMCLUHAN19//TPStory/Obituaries" class="external text" title="http://www.theglobeandmail.com/servlet/story/LAC.20080419.OBMCLUHAN19//TPStory/Obituaries" rel="nofollow">"She was Marshall McLuhan's great love ardent defender, supporter and critic"</a>. <i>Globe and Mail</i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.theglobeandmail.com/servlet/story/LAC.20080419.OBMCLUHAN19//TPStory/Obituaries" class="external free" title="http://www.theglobeandmail.com/servlet/story/LAC.20080419.OBMCLUHAN19//TPStory/Obituaries" rel="nofollow">http://www.theglobeandmail.com/servlet/story/LAC.20080419.OBMCLUHAN19//TPStory/Obituaries</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-06-29</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=She+was+Marshall+McLuhan%27s+great+love+ardent+defender%2C+supporter+and+critic&amp;rft.atitle=Globe+and+Mail&amp;rft.aulast=Fitterman&amp;rft.aufirst=Lisa&amp;rft.au=Fitterman%2C+Lisa&amp;rft.date=%5B%5B2008-04-19%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.theglobeandmail.com%2Fservlet%2Fstory%2FLAC.20080419.OBMCLUHAN19%2F%2FTPStory%2FObituaries&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Marshall_McLuhan"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
